A national survey conducted by the Diabetic Association of Pakistan (DAP) reveals that there are now some 4.3 million diabetics in Pakistan and the figure is likely to reach 14.5 million by 2025.
The number of diabetes cases in the world is forecast to nearly double to reach 220 million by the year 2010, according to a report published today.
We live in a society in which people drive instead of walk, fast food is available 24 hours a day, children are bombarded with advertisements for junk food, and one-quarter of all the vegetables we eat are french fries.
